762
00:50:39,404 --> 00:50:42,573
Right.

763
00:50:42,573 --> 00:50:44,875
Does that mean
he's not coming on, then?

764
00:50:44,875 --> 00:50:47,812
No, James, he's not.

765
00:50:47,812 --> 00:50:51,116
It's okay, though.
We anticipated
this sort of thing,

766
00:50:51,116 --> 00:50:53,151
so we got
a back-up guest ready.

767
00:50:53,151 --> 00:50:55,186
Uh...

768
00:50:55,186 --> 00:50:57,555
He was in Man From Uncle.

769
00:50:57,555 --> 00:51:00,991
He was in Lone Ranger.
He was both twins

770
00:51:00,991 --> 00:51:02,760
in The Social Network.

771
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:05,530
And his new film is called
Nocturnal Animals.

772
00:51:05,530 --> 00:51:07,565
We haven't had time,
unfortunately,

773
00:51:07,565 --> 00:51:09,500
to organize
a dramatic entrance,

774
00:51:09,500 --> 00:51:12,337
but I hope you'll give him
a warm welcome nevertheless.

775
00:51:12,337 --> 00:51:14,739
Ladies and gentlemen,
Armie Hammer!

776
00:51:15,973 --> 00:51:17,842
There he is.

777
00:51:18,943 --> 00:51:20,978
Oh, my...

778
00:51:20,978 --> 00:51:22,680
Jesus!

779
00:51:22,680 --> 00:51:24,482
Is that a snake?

780
00:51:24,482 --> 00:51:26,384
- It's a snake.
- That's a rattlesnake.

781
00:51:26,384 --> 00:51:28,386
- Is it?
- Yeah.

782
00:51:28,386 --> 00:51:31,289
He's being killed.
Quiet, everyone.

783
00:51:31,289 --> 00:51:33,324
Quiet, please.

784
00:51:33,324 --> 00:51:35,360
There's literally
nothing we can do.

785
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:37,395
He's yards away from us.

786
00:51:37,395 --> 00:51:39,063
Snakes are like herds
of them.

787
00:51:39,063 --> 00:51:41,766
- They hunt in packs.
- Yeah, they're pack animals.

788
00:51:41,766 --> 00:51:44,535
Does that mean
he's not coming on either?

789
00:51:44,535 --> 00:51:47,805
No, James, he's finished
writhing around in agony.

790
00:51:47,805 --> 00:51:49,840
And now he's dead.

791
00:51:49,840 --> 00:51:51,876
So that is a no.

792
00:51:51,876 --> 00:51:53,711
Well, uh...

793
00:51:53,711 --> 00:51:56,281
maybe there's somebody famous
in the audience.

794
00:51:56,281 --> 00:51:58,283
That's unlikely.

795
00:51:58,283 --> 00:52:00,751
No. Seriously,
you know Carol Vorderman?

796
00:52:00,751 --> 00:52:03,321
She rang me this morning
from an air show nearby

797
00:52:03,321 --> 00:52:06,357
and said,
can she come to the show?

798
00:52:06,357 --> 00:52:08,359
I know you don't know
who Carol Vorderman is.

799
00:52:08,359 --> 00:52:10,895
She's a huge, huge,
huge star in the UK.

800
00:52:10,895 --> 00:52:12,930
She started out on
a program called Countdown

801
00:52:12,930 --> 00:52:15,200
and established herself as
being unbelievably brilliant,

802
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:17,202
a fantastic mathematician

803
00:52:17,202 --> 00:52:19,237
and very beautiful.

804
00:52:19,237 --> 00:52:22,540
Yes, she's also dead.

805
00:52:22,540 --> 00:52:24,074
What?

806
00:52:24,074 --> 00:52:27,878
- What?
- She's dead.

807
00:52:27,878 --> 00:52:30,648
- How did that happen?
- I don't know.
I'm not a pathologist!

808
00:52:30,648 --> 00:52:33,284
But she's dead
is what she is.

809
00:52:33,284 --> 00:52:35,286
- Seriously?
- Yes!

810
00:52:35,286 --> 00:52:38,289
- Christ.
- Problem.

811
00:52:38,289 --> 00:52:40,591
What are we gonna do?

812
00:52:40,591 --> 00:52:41,859
Um...

813
00:52:41,859 --> 00:52:44,229
Jesus, look at that out there.
It's like a--

814
00:52:44,229 --> 00:52:45,863
It's just littered
with corpses.

815
00:52:48,333 --> 00:52:51,836
Lads, I don't think
this bit is working.

816
00:52:51,836 --> 00:52:53,238
Let's drop

817
00:52:53,238 --> 00:52:55,573
Celebrity Brain Crash
this week.

818
00:52:55,573 --> 00:52:57,708
We'll do it again in
South Africa next week,

819
00:52:57,708 --> 00:52:59,744
and I think people will
have forgotten all this.

820
00:52:59,744 --> 00:53:02,513
- They might not.
- I think they will.

821
00:53:02,513 --> 00:53:04,949
We'll just skip over it now.
It's not gonna happen.

822
00:53:04,949 --> 00:53:07,285
That's okay, 'cause we
can back to the cars.

823
00:53:07,285 --> 00:53:10,388
Yes! Moving on!

824
00:53:11,689 --> 00:53:14,091
- Don't look.
- Yes, don't look.

825
00:53:14,091 --> 00:53:15,460
This week--

826
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:17,762
This week we are trying
to find out

827
00:53:17,762 --> 00:53:20,531
which of the new breed of
hybrid hypercars is the best.

828
00:53:20,531 --> 00:53:22,900
Yes. On day one
at the track in Portugal,

829
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:26,404
we established that
the McLaren P1 is a mentalist,

830
00:53:26,404 --> 00:53:30,174
that the Porsche 918
is a very good milk float,

831
00:53:30,174 --> 00:53:33,444
and that the Ferrari LaFerrari
can do nothing at all.

832
00:53:34,345 --> 00:53:36,381
Some of that is true.

833
00:53:36,381 --> 00:53:39,484
But now, day two.

834
00:53:49,660 --> 00:53:51,629
We began by lining up

835
00:53:51,629 --> 00:53:54,365
the three most exciting cars
on the planet

836
00:53:54,365 --> 00:53:58,002
for the drag race
of all drag races.

837
00:54:12,016 --> 00:54:15,686
Naturally, this meant
engaging launch control,

838
00:54:15,686 --> 00:54:20,024
which in the McLaren
takes about a fortnight.

839
00:54:20,024 --> 00:54:24,094
I have to have the drive tray
in track mode,

840
00:54:24,094 --> 00:54:26,331
the aero package
in sport mode,

841
00:54:26,331 --> 00:54:27,665
so that the rear end squats

842
00:54:27,665 --> 00:54:29,634
when I set off
and gives me more traction.

843
00:54:29,634 --> 00:54:32,870
I have to have the DRS
button pressed with my thumb

844
00:54:32,870 --> 00:54:36,874
to keep the rear wing open
which reduces drag obviously.

845
00:54:36,874 --> 00:54:39,977
Launch control in the Porsche,
left foot on the brake hard.

846
00:54:39,977 --> 00:54:42,012
Right foot
on the throttle hard.

847
00:54:42,012 --> 00:54:44,349
Light goes green, left foot
off brake. Pa-ching!

848
00:54:44,349 --> 00:54:46,751
Launch button,
press for two seconds.

849
00:54:46,751 --> 00:54:49,520
Left foot on brake.
Right foot on throttle.

850
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:51,956
Press launch control,
mash the throttle,

851
00:54:51,956 --> 00:54:54,759
within four seconds
release the brake.

852
00:54:54,759 --> 00:54:57,995
Three seconds later,
I have full boost,

853
00:54:57,995 --> 00:55:00,431
and I have to set off
within three seconds

854
00:55:00,431 --> 00:55:02,833
or the entire system
disengages.

855
00:55:02,833 --> 00:55:05,603
I'm going to get this wrong.

856
00:55:05,603 --> 00:55:07,638
Just so you know.

857
00:55:07,638 --> 00:55:09,940
I've got a lot to do in here.

858
00:55:36,401 --> 00:55:39,169
I wasn't ready.

859
00:55:39,169 --> 00:55:41,939
Oh, my God!
That is quick!

860
00:55:45,810 --> 00:55:49,947
Holy mother!
Did you see that?

861
00:55:49,947 --> 00:55:53,183
- me!
- Jesus Christ!

862
00:55:53,183 --> 00:55:55,119
It's all over the place.

863
00:56:00,458 --> 00:56:03,060
Since it was clear I'd got
all my buttons wrong,

864
00:56:03,060 --> 00:56:06,497
the chaps agreed
to another run.

865
00:56:06,497 --> 00:56:08,533
Sit rep,
the lights went green

866
00:56:08,533 --> 00:56:10,601
before the boost was ready,

867
00:56:10,601 --> 00:56:12,770
and I had the DRS button
still pressed

868
00:56:12,770 --> 00:56:15,440
when I got to the end,
which meant I had no downforce,

869
00:56:15,440 --> 00:56:18,643
which meant--
Well, poo came out.

870
00:56:18,643 --> 00:56:22,713
This time I'm gonna do it
with more drag,

871
00:56:22,713 --> 00:56:25,315
which will slow me down,
but I will be able to stop

872
00:56:25,315 --> 00:56:27,452
without killing myself.

873
00:56:32,457 --> 00:56:34,559
KERS system charged. Right.

874
00:56:39,196 --> 00:56:41,566
Boost building.

875
00:56:44,368 --> 00:56:46,504
Three, two...

876
00:56:50,475 --> 00:56:52,543
And we are away!
What a start!

877
00:56:55,312 --> 00:56:57,715
The Porsche has got off
to a flyer.

878
00:56:59,216 --> 00:57:01,151
Oh, balls!

879
00:57:02,620 --> 00:57:04,889
180, 190, 210.

880
00:57:06,691 --> 00:57:08,726
230 kilometers an hour.

881
00:57:14,198 --> 00:57:16,967
That wasn't very good.

882
00:57:16,967 --> 00:57:20,204
Because James had
somehow messed up that time,

883
00:57:20,204 --> 00:57:22,673
and because this test
was about the cars,

884
00:57:22,673 --> 00:57:25,209
we decided to go again.

885
00:57:30,347 --> 00:57:31,782
It's a rocket ship.

886
00:57:33,518 --> 00:57:35,620
For England!

887
00:57:37,254 --> 00:57:38,989
No, no!

888
00:57:44,729 --> 00:57:46,997
Okay, we have all three
won this now.

889
00:57:49,634 --> 00:57:51,902
Determined
to find a definitive

890
00:57:51,902 --> 00:57:55,405
one-two-three
finishing order,

891
00:57:55,405 --> 00:57:57,274
we ran again.

892
00:58:02,212 --> 00:58:06,216
Another totally different
result there, gentlemen.

893
00:58:07,384 --> 00:58:08,819
And again.

894
00:58:11,956 --> 00:58:15,760
That's a different result
again.

895
00:58:15,760 --> 00:58:17,895
And again?

896
00:58:23,100 --> 00:58:25,369
At this point,
we decided to call

897
00:58:25,369 --> 00:58:26,937
a halt to proceedings,

898
00:58:26,937 --> 00:58:31,609
because we had reached
a scientific conclusion.

899
00:58:31,609 --> 00:58:35,045
It turns out it doesn't really
matter which car you buy,

900
00:58:35,045 --> 00:58:37,281
it all depends on your shoes.

901
00:58:37,281 --> 00:58:38,983
Now, this is a TOD loafer.

902
00:58:38,983 --> 00:58:42,052
Slightly worn
to get a crisper jump

903
00:58:42,052 --> 00:58:44,254
off the brake pedal,
and it's immediate.

904
00:58:44,254 --> 00:58:47,191
- This is a Converse.
- There's more sponge
in there than I thought.

905
00:58:47,191 --> 00:58:50,160
See, Adidas, they weren't
thinking that through.

906
00:58:50,160 --> 00:58:53,330
- So, as you lift
your foot up--
- It's a millisecond.

907
00:58:53,330 --> 00:58:54,699
I know you've got KERS,

908
00:58:54,699 --> 00:58:56,266
I know you've got
a 6.3-litre V12,

909
00:58:56,266 --> 00:58:58,836
and I know that launch
control system is amazing,

910
00:58:58,836 --> 00:59:00,237
but it's all let down

911
00:59:00,237 --> 00:59:02,206
by the sponginess
of the Adidas shoe.

912
00:59:02,206 --> 00:59:04,441
So they should sell you
the car and the shoes.

913
00:59:04,441 --> 00:59:06,977
No, have you got the correct
shoes and have you worn them in?

914
00:59:06,977 --> 00:59:09,013
- Exactly.
- Fresh shoes, lads.

915
00:59:09,013 --> 00:59:13,217
- I just need to--
- You need to skid about.
There we go.

916
00:59:13,217 --> 00:59:15,820
With that sorted,

917
00:59:15,820 --> 00:59:18,055
it was time to bring in
a racing driver

918
00:59:18,055 --> 00:59:21,926
to see which of our cars
could do the fastest lap.

919
00:59:21,926 --> 00:59:25,262
Our resident American
said he wasn't interested,

920
00:59:25,262 --> 00:59:28,265
because all three cars
are probably communist.

921
00:59:28,265 --> 00:59:31,636
So instead, we went
for a Belgian chap--

922
00:59:33,170 --> 00:59:36,807
...who's done Formula One
and Formula E,

923
00:59:36,807 --> 00:59:39,343
Jerome d'Ambrosio.

924
00:59:44,314 --> 00:59:46,016
Jerome took the cars out

925
00:59:46,016 --> 00:59:48,686
to get a sense of how
they handled.

926
01:00:05,002 --> 01:00:06,837
And when he'd finished,

927
01:00:06,837 --> 01:00:08,639
we were interested to hear

928
01:00:08,639 --> 01:00:10,607
his professional opinion.

929
01:00:54,785 --> 01:00:57,421
At this point,
word reached us that Jeremy

930
01:00:57,421 --> 01:01:01,091
was taking liberties
with the subtitling machine.

931
01:01:02,459 --> 01:01:05,429
So we moved on
to the big event:

932
01:01:05,429 --> 01:01:08,098
the timed laps.

933
01:01:13,437 --> 01:01:15,472
Once the mechanics had
finished their preparations,

934
01:01:15,472 --> 01:01:18,408
the three speed traps
were activated.

935
01:01:21,879 --> 01:01:24,548
And the Ferrari LaFerrari
took its place

936
01:01:24,548 --> 01:01:27,051
on the start line.

937
01:01:28,185 --> 01:01:30,220
Look how good it looks there.

938
01:01:30,220 --> 01:01:33,557
This is just wasting time.
It's wasting rubber and fuel.

939
01:01:33,557 --> 01:01:35,392
No, this is like
an amuse-bouche.

940
01:01:35,392 --> 01:01:39,096
Yeah, it is. You have ordered
the duck and sherry trifle.

941
01:01:39,096 --> 01:01:42,833
- And you're a melon ball.
- I'm not even listening.

942
01:01:58,448 --> 01:02:03,453
Gentlemen, it is doing
231.4 kilometers an hour

943
01:02:03,453 --> 01:02:05,589
at the end of the straight.

944
01:02:05,589 --> 01:02:09,193
It's about the same speed
as a Golf diesel,
something like that.

945
01:02:22,840 --> 01:02:26,276
194.9.

946
01:02:26,276 --> 01:02:28,112
Going down the hill
using gravity.

947
01:02:28,112 --> 01:02:30,314
- Is he stopping off
for shopping?
- He must be.

948
01:02:45,963 --> 01:02:48,098
Here he is.

949
01:02:54,604 --> 01:02:59,343
- James, if you want
to get a cup of tea.
- We've warmed the track.

950
01:02:59,343 --> 01:03:03,848
Next it was the turn
of the Porsche 918.

951
01:03:03,848 --> 01:03:06,350
How much faster will it go
because of the stripes?

952
01:03:06,350 --> 01:03:07,351
Much.

953
01:03:22,299 --> 01:03:24,134
231 point...

954
01:03:24,134 --> 01:03:26,170
So he's faster
than the Ferrari.

955
01:03:35,679 --> 01:03:38,182
183.0.

956
01:03:38,182 --> 01:03:41,785
Way, way,
way slower than him.

957
01:03:41,785 --> 01:03:43,921
Don't forget between here
and the next measuring point,

958
01:03:43,921 --> 01:03:46,590
Okay, you've got
four slow corners,

959
01:03:46,590 --> 01:03:49,259
and those are the ones
where the Porsche
is gonna make up time.

960
01:03:51,161 --> 01:03:52,362
Because of the
four-wheel steering.

961
01:03:52,362 --> 01:03:56,033
- Like a Honda Prelude?
- No!

962
01:04:09,646 --> 01:04:12,449
- 110 point what?
- One.

963
01:04:12,449 --> 01:04:16,386
So, almost to a tenth
of a kilometer an hour,
the same speed as you.

964
01:04:21,258 --> 01:04:24,061
Here he comes.
He's firing noises.

965
01:04:25,362 --> 01:04:26,931
There it is.
Look at that.

966
01:04:29,833 --> 01:04:33,337
Finally, it was
the turn of the psycho killer.

967
01:04:33,337 --> 01:04:36,040
The trickiest,
the edgiest of the three.

968
01:04:37,541 --> 01:04:39,443
But I was so confident
it'd win,

969
01:04:39,443 --> 01:04:43,047
I was prepared
to take a massive gamble.

970
01:04:44,381 --> 01:04:49,086
If the McLaren
isn't the fastest,

971
01:04:49,086 --> 01:04:51,956
you two can knock
my house down.

972
01:04:51,956 --> 01:04:54,124
- What?
- Knock it down.

973
01:04:54,124 --> 01:04:56,994
- What, your house?
- Yeah, and I mean that.

974
01:04:56,994 --> 01:05:00,664
That's how confident I am
that that will be the fastest.

975
01:05:00,664 --> 01:05:04,801
- You know we will do that?
- Yeah.

976
01:05:04,801 --> 01:05:07,271
- It's a serious bet?
- Yeah.

977
01:05:07,271 --> 01:05:09,839
- Fine.
- If that's not the fastest,

978
01:05:09,839 --> 01:05:12,409
- we can knock your house down?
- Yup.

979
01:05:12,409 --> 01:05:14,644
You know where it is.
You've both been.

980
01:05:14,644 --> 01:05:16,613
I'd love to knock it down.

981
01:05:23,020 --> 01:05:25,222
Here we go.
A lot riding on this.

982
01:05:37,834 --> 01:05:41,305
235.9.

983
01:05:41,305 --> 01:05:44,008
Okay, it's fastest at the end
of the first straight.

984
01:05:48,712 --> 01:05:50,747
Would you like to come
to my house for dinner?

985
01:05:50,747 --> 01:05:52,549
Yes. Can I bring a bulldozer?

986
01:06:00,324 --> 01:06:02,192
188.3.

987
01:06:02,192 --> 01:06:04,228
That is worryingly quick.
Brisk.

988
01:06:04,228 --> 01:06:06,063
It's quite brisk?

989
01:06:06,063 --> 01:06:08,865
We don't know how fast it's
going around the tight turns.

990
01:06:08,865 --> 01:06:11,435
Might have been doing
two kilometers an hour
around here.

991
01:06:23,180 --> 01:06:25,382
Where is he?

992
01:06:25,382 --> 01:06:26,616
Crashed.

993
01:06:44,068 --> 01:06:46,936
With that,
back to the tent.

994
01:06:54,811 --> 01:06:56,646
Thank you so much. Now...

995
01:06:56,646 --> 01:06:58,682
I want to make it
absolutely plain,

996
01:06:58,682 --> 01:07:00,717
'cause I know this matters
to anoraks,

997
01:07:00,717 --> 01:07:06,156
all three cars were running
on exactly the same sort
of tires.

998
01:07:06,156 --> 01:07:08,758
Yes, same tires, same track,
same driver.

999
01:07:08,758 --> 01:07:11,095
So the times
are down to the cars.

1000
01:07:11,095 --> 01:07:14,331
Yup. And now it is time
to reveal those times.

1001
01:07:14,331 --> 01:07:16,533
Let me just make it
absolutely clear.

1002
01:07:16,533 --> 01:07:18,102
We don't know what they are.

1003
01:07:18,102 --> 01:07:20,270
The producers have kept them
from us.

1004
01:07:20,270 --> 01:07:21,605
- They're top secret.
- Yup.

1005
01:07:21,605 --> 01:07:23,773
So, let's put
the scoreboard up,

1006
01:07:23,773 --> 01:07:25,008
and let's begin with

1007
01:07:25,008 --> 01:07:27,644
the Ferrari LaFerrari,
I believe.

1008
01:07:27,644 --> 01:07:30,114
Let's see what it did it in,
please.

1009
01:07:33,883 --> 01:07:36,953
We don't know
if that's any good, do we?

1010
01:07:36,953 --> 01:07:39,323
Let's move on
and do the Porsche next.

1011
01:07:39,323 --> 01:07:40,790
What did the Porsche
do it in?

1012
01:07:42,192 --> 01:07:46,630
Oh, yes! 1:54.2!

1013
01:07:46,630 --> 01:07:49,533
Yes! Yes! You see?

1014
01:07:49,533 --> 01:07:51,668
You said it would mince
the Porsche.

1015
01:07:51,668 --> 01:07:55,038
And it didn't mince it.
It was slower than the Porsche.

1016
01:07:55,038 --> 01:07:56,906
I told you
it's just a melon ball.

1017
01:07:56,906 --> 01:07:58,842
It's slower than my car,

1018
01:07:58,842 --> 01:08:01,378
which was faster
than your car.

1019
01:08:01,378 --> 01:08:03,613
0.2 of a second,
and it looks better.

1020
01:08:03,613 --> 01:08:06,350
Yeah, it did in my mirror
where it belongs getting
smaller.

1021
01:08:06,350 --> 01:08:07,951
It's a melon ball,
and it lost.

1022
01:08:07,951 --> 01:08:09,186
- Hammond.
- What?

1023
01:08:09,186 --> 01:08:10,954
- Calm down.
- All right.

1024
01:08:10,954 --> 01:08:12,156
Because now we must bring up

1025
01:08:12,156 --> 01:08:13,723
the time that really matters.

1026
01:08:13,723 --> 01:08:17,294
The one where
a lot's at stake.

1027
01:08:17,294 --> 01:08:18,295
The McLaren...

1028
01:08:18,295 --> 01:08:19,463
The McLaren P1.

1029
01:08:19,463 --> 01:08:22,166
- Are you nervous? Sure?
- No. No.

1030
01:08:22,166 --> 01:08:23,500
- A little bit?
- No!

1031
01:08:23,500 --> 01:08:25,269
- I'm not nervous.
- Why be nervous?

1032
01:08:25,269 --> 01:08:26,470
You could get, like,
a shopping trolley

1033
01:08:26,470 --> 01:08:28,705
and keep all your things
in it.

1034
01:08:28,705 --> 01:08:31,575
Make some new friends
under a bridge somewhere.

1035
01:08:31,575 --> 01:08:33,843
- Hammond.
- I'd say sell your body
but don't do that.

1036
01:08:33,843 --> 01:08:36,580
Be quiet! Let's--

1037
01:08:36,580 --> 01:08:39,316
Let's bring up the time
of the P1. Here we go.

1038
01:08:39,316 --> 01:08:42,419
- Oh, God.
- Where is it?

1039
01:08:50,093 --> 01:08:52,462
Yes!

1040
01:08:56,666 --> 01:09:00,404
That is funny.
Because you said...

1041
01:09:00,404 --> 01:09:03,207
the fastest,
but it's not the fastest.

1042
01:09:03,207 --> 01:09:05,209
It's the slowest!

1043
01:09:05,209 --> 01:09:08,445
Ladies and gentlemen,
journalist, broadcaster

1044
01:09:08,445 --> 01:09:11,881
and homeless man,
Jeremy Clarkson.

1045
01:09:18,788 --> 01:09:23,560
That's what it is.
That's what it is.

1046
01:09:23,560 --> 01:09:26,363
You're not really going
to knock my house down?

1047
01:09:26,363 --> 01:09:28,865
Yes, we are.

1048
01:09:28,865 --> 01:09:30,900
- A bet is a bet.
- That's the deal.

1049
01:09:30,900 --> 01:09:33,637
- And we're going to film it.
- No, but the thing is,

1050
01:09:33,637 --> 01:09:36,240
on the tires that the
McLaren can be bought with,

1051
01:09:36,240 --> 01:09:38,575
it was faster.

1052
01:09:38,575 --> 01:09:40,277
We agreed right at the start

1053
01:09:40,277 --> 01:09:43,380
we'd all run on
the same tires.

1054
01:09:43,380 --> 01:09:45,849
That was the deal
before your car lost.

1055
01:09:45,849 --> 01:09:47,384
So let's just...

1056
01:09:47,384 --> 01:09:50,887
Let's just sum this
first show up, shall we?

1057
01:09:50,887 --> 01:09:52,722
I've lost my house.

1058
01:09:52,722 --> 01:09:55,091
- We've had a fight
with the audience.
- Big one.

1059
01:09:55,091 --> 01:09:57,961
Somebody shot our drone down.

1060
01:09:57,961 --> 01:10:00,664
And we've killed three
quite major celebrities.

1061
01:10:00,664 --> 01:10:02,699
Yeah, but on the plus side,

1062
01:10:02,699 --> 01:10:04,901
my Porsche was the fastest!

1063
01:10:10,407 --> 01:10:12,576
And on that terrible
disappointment,

1064
01:10:12,576 --> 01:10:14,678
I'm afraid it's time to end.

1065
01:10:14,678 --> 01:10:16,480
Thank you all very much
for coming.

1066
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:18,014
Thank you for watching.

1067
01:10:18,014 --> 01:10:19,883
And we'll see you next week
in Johannesburg.

1068
01:10:19,883 --> 01:10:21,285
Good-bye!

